# OpenTelemetry Environment Variable Examples

These examples are local notes. They are not applied automatically to Kubernetes manifests.

```bash
OTEL_SERVICE_NAME={{ service_name }}
OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT={{ tracing.collector.endpoint }}
OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_PROTOCOL={{ otel_protocol }}
OTEL_RESOURCE_ATTRIBUTES=service.name={{ service_name }},deployment.environment=local,k8s.namespace.name={{ app.namespace }}
```

{% if tracing.collector.protocol == "otlp-http" -%}
`otlp-http` commonly uses port `4318` and protocol value `http/protobuf`.
{% else -%}
`otlp-grpc` commonly uses port `4317` and protocol value `grpc`.
{% endif %}

Adapt these variables to the language SDK, framework, and runtime used by the application.
